---
Description: Finding architectural, implementation, or organizational information
alwaysApply: true
---

When working on files within a directory, first read the README.md file in the directory. It will contain organizational and possibly architectural or implementation information for the directory.

Also, look for a "./docs" directory. Read all the files in the documents directory for architectural and implementation information on the directory.

When starting work on a directory, notify the user that you have read the README.md or the documents in the ./docs directory. 